/ CALLING CONVENTION: Functions return to 1P and accept arguments from 4P

FIM 4P 36 /"$ " for monitor
JMS WCR
FIM 4P 32
JMS WCR


/ Keyboard polling loop
/ Set expecting_char to 0 (false)
LDM 0
XCH 4R
PKB, JMS RKB
    / Set the accumulator to 0 if the key is the character separator
    LDM 1000B
    XCH 0R
    LD 2R
    SUB 0R
    JCN 0100B SEP / Jump to the separator-handling code if the accumulator is 0
    CHR, LD 4R
        JCN 0100B PKB / If expecting_char is 0 (false), ignore the char
        / Otherwise, write the char to the monitor
        LD 2R
        XCH 8R
        LD 3R
        XCH 9R
        JMS WCR
        / Set expecting_char to 0 (false)
        LDM 0
        XCH 4R
        JUN PKB
    SEP, LDM 1 / Set expecting_char to 1 (true)
        XCH 4R
        JUN PKB


/ Read from keyboard - RKB()
RKB, FIM 0P 0
    SRC 0P
    RDR
    XCH 2R

    FIM 0P 1
    SRC 0P
    RDR
    XCH 3R

    BBL 0

/ Write Char to monitor - WCR(char: 8)
WCR, LDM 2 / Write the char separator
    XCH 1R
    SRC 0P
    LDM 8
    WRR

    JMS WT / Wait for the monitor to receive it

    LDM 3 / Write the actual character
    XCH 1R
    SRC 0P
    LD 9R
    WRR
    LDM 2
    XCH 1R
    SRC 0P
    LD 8R
    WRR

    JMS WT / Wait for the monitor to receive it

    BBL 0

/ Wait - WT()
WT, NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
NOP
BBL 0
